17/12/2009
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- Former Bosnian Serb commander Zdravko Tolimir pleaded not guilty Wednesday (December 16th) to genocide and other crimes stemming from the 1995 Srebrenica massacre. Tolimir, an aide to former Bosnian Serb military leader Ratko Mladic, was arrested in June 2007. No date has been set for the start of his trial at The Hague. 
In other news Wednesday, the UN Security Council extended the mandate of the war crimes tribunal through the end of 2012. By that time, the tribunal should have concluded all appeals procedures. Trial judges are to finish their work by June 30th 2010. (Tanjug - 17/12/09; Xinhua, UN News Centre, RTS, BHRT, Fena, AP - 16/12/09)
